# Premium UI Implementation

**Part of Premium UI Standards** (Split 4 of 4)

**See also**:
- @42-spacing-layout.mdc - Spacing and typography foundations
- @43-visual-design.mdc - Colors, surfaces, borders, iconography
- @44-components-motion.mdc - Buttons, inputs, lists, motion

---

## 1. Accessibility Rules (Luxury Must Still Be Usable)

### 1.1 Touch Targets

**Rule**: Minimum `44×44px` touch targets (iOS/Android standard).

**Implementation**:
```typescript
<TouchableOpacity
  style={{
    minWidth: 44,
    minHeight: 44,
    padding: SPACING[2],
  }}
>
  <Icon size={20} />
</TouchableOpacity>
```

---

### 1.2 Contrast

**Rule**: Meet WCAG AA where possible (4.5:1 minimum contrast for normal text).

**Reference**: See @19-accessibility-rules.mdc for complete accessibility guidelines.

---

### 1.3 State Communication

**Rule**: Do not communicate state by color alone. Add icon/text.

**✅ GOOD**:
```typescript
<View style={{ flexDirection: 'row', alignItems: 'center' }}>
  <Icon name="check-circle" color={theme.status.success} />
  <Text style={{ color: theme.status.success }}>Active</Text>
</View>
```

**❌ BAD**:
```typescript
// Color only (inaccessible)
<View style={{ backgroundColor: theme.status.success }} />
```

---

## 2. Design Tokens (Mandatory)

### 2.1 No Hard-Coded Values

**Rule**: No hard-coded hex values or spacing in components (except in the token file).

**✅ GOOD**:
```typescript
import { SPACING, BORDER_RADIUS } from '@/shared/constants/spacing';
import { theme } from '@/infrastructure/theme/theme-context';

<View style={{
  padding: SPACING[4],
  borderRadius: BORDER_RADIUS.md,
  backgroundColor: theme.background.primary,
}} />
```

**❌ BAD**:
```typescript
<View style={{
  padding: 16,              // Hard-coded!
  borderRadius: 8,         // Hard-coded!
  backgroundColor: '#FFFFFF', // Hard-coded!
}} />
```

**Token Files**:
- `src/shared/constants/spacing.ts` - All spacing values
- `src/shared/constants/typography.ts` - All typography values
- `src/shared/constants/colors.ts` - All color values (if not using theme)
- `src/infrastructure/theme/theme-context.tsx` - Theme colors

---

## 3. Component Architecture

### 3.1 Use a Single Screen Wrapper

**Rule**: All screens should use the same scaffolding: safe area handling, background color, default padding, standard header behavior.

**Screen Wrapper Component**:
```typescript
// src/presentation/components/screen-wrapper.tsx
export const ScreenWrapper: React.FC<{
  children: React.ReactNode;
  padding?: number;
  backgroundColor?: string;
}> = ({ children, padding = SPACING[5], backgroundColor }) => {
  const { theme } = useTheme();
  const insets = useSafeAreaInsets();

  return (
    <SafeAreaView
      style={{
        flex: 1,
        backgroundColor: backgroundColor || theme.background.primary,
        paddingTop: insets.top,
        paddingBottom: insets.bottom,
      }}
    >
      <View style={{ flex: 1, paddingHorizontal: padding }}>
        {children}
      </View>
    </SafeAreaView>
  );
};

// Usage in all screens
export default function MyScreen() {
  return (
    <ScreenWrapper>
      {/* Screen content */}
    </ScreenWrapper>
  );
}
```

---

### 3.2 Enforce Component "Tiers"

**Rule**: Text → AppText (typography preset required). View → Surface/Card (surface type required). Touchable → Button (variant required).

**Component Hierarchy**:
```typescript
// Tier 1: Base components (must use tokens)
export const AppText: React.FC<{
  variant: keyof typeof TEXT_STYLES;
  children: React.ReactNode;
}> = ({ variant, children, style }) => {
  return (
    <Text style={[TEXT_STYLES[variant], style]}>
      {children}
    </Text>
  );
};

// Tier 2: Surface components
export const Surface: React.FC<{
  variant: 'default' | 'raised' | 'overlay';
  children: React.ReactNode;
}> = ({ variant, children, style }) => {
  const { theme } = useTheme();
  return (
    <View style={[
      { backgroundColor: theme.surface[variant] },
      style,
    ]}>
      {children}
    </View>
  );
};

// Tier 3: Interactive components
export const Button: React.FC<{
  variant: 'primary' | 'secondary' | 'destructive';
  title: string;
  onPress: () => void;
}> = ({ variant, title, onPress }) => {
  // Implementation with required variant
};
```

**❌ FORBIDDEN**: Creating arbitrary styles easily. If a dev can't create arbitrary styles easily, consistency improves automatically.

---

## 4. Recommended Defaults (Strong Starting Point)

If you want a strong starting point, use these defaults:

- **Screen padding**: `SPACING[5]` (20px)
- **Card radius**: `BORDER_RADIUS.md` (14-16px)
- **Button height**: `50px` (48-52 range)
- **Border width**: `StyleSheet.hairlineWidth` or `1`
- **Body text**: `16px` with `1.4×` line height
- **Shadows**: Used only for modals and floating bars

---

## 5. Implementation Checklist

Before marking a component/screen "complete":

- [ ] All spacing uses 8pt grid tokens (4, 8, 12, 16, 20, 24, 32, 40, 48)
- [ ] No hard-coded colors, spacing, or typography values
- [ ] Text uses one of the 8 allowed text styles
- [ ] Colors follow 85-95% neutrals, 3-10% primary, 0.5-3% accent rule
- [ ] No pure black (#000000) or pure white (#FFFFFF)
- [ ] Borders preferred over shadows (except modals)
- [ ] Consistent border radius scale
- [ ] Buttons are 48-52px height
- [ ] Inputs are 48-52px height with labels above
- [ ] List rows are 56-64px height
- [ ] Touch targets minimum 44×44px
- [ ] Animations are 150-220ms micro-animations
- [ ] No bouncy transitions (except subtle toggles)
- [ ] Skeleton loading for lists, spinners only for short actions
- [ ] One icon library, one style (all outline or all filled)
- [ ] Content is minimal (fewer labels, shorter copy, more whitespace)
- [ ] Numbers use tabular numerals and consistent formatting
- [ ] Screen uses ScreenWrapper component
- [ ] Components use enforced tiers (AppText, Surface, Button)

